24. How to Access ADP's Employee Resource Center 

Welcome to ADP's Employee Resource Center, where employees can access important information about their payroll, benefits, and other HR-related matters. In this article, we will guide you through the steps to access ADP's Employee Resource Center, so you can get the information you need in a timely and efficient manner.

Step 1: Visit the ADP website
The first step to accessing the Employee Resource Center is to visit the ADP website at www.adp.com. Once you are on the website, look for the login button on the top right corner of the homepage.

Step 2: Enter your login credentials
Next, you will need to enter your login credentials, which include your username and password. If you have not created an account yet, you will need to do so before you can access the Employee Resource Center. Simply click on the "create account" button and follow the prompts to set up your account.

Step 3: Navigate to the Employee Resource Center
Once you have logged in to your account, you will be directed to your dashboard. From there, you can access the Employee Resource Center by clicking on the "HR and Payroll" tab on the left-hand side of the screen. This will take you to the main HR and Payroll page, which houses a variety of useful resources and tools for employees.

Step 4: Find the information you need
Within the Employee Resource Center, you will find a wealth of information and resources at your fingertips. Depending on your needs and interests, you can explore various sections such as "Pay and Taxes," "Benefits," "Time and Attendance," and "Company Information." Each section contains a variety of articles, videos, and other resources that can help answer your questions and provide guidance on various HR-related matters.

Step 5: Contact ADP customer support if you need additional assistance
If you are unable to find the information you need within the Employee Resource Center, you can always reach out to ADP's customer support team for assistance. Simply click on the "Contact Us" button on the top right corner of the homepage and select the appropriate option for your inquiry. You can also call the customer care center at 1-800-225-5237 to speak with a representative directly.

In conclusion, ADP's Employee Resource Center provides employees with a comprehensive set of tools and resources to help them manage their payroll, benefits, and other HR-related matters. By following the simple steps outlined in this article, you can quickly and easily access the Employee Resource Center and find the information you need to stay informed and empowered at work.